[6] Cholera - Nigeria (Kaduna)
Date: Sat, 10 Sep 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200509/10/eng20050910_207744.html>

10 persons died and several others were hospitalized following an
outbreak of cholera in the central Nigerian state of Kaduna, state
media reported Fri, 9 Sep 2005. The outbreak occurred at the city
of Kafanchan, and had been confirmed by local council chairman
Abraham Jatau, the News Agency of Nigeria reported.
"We have already taken necessary steps to control the situation,"
Jatau was quoted as saying, advising local residents to adopt good
sanitary habits in their daily lives. "The victims are responding to
treatment and the council, through its emergency relief committee,
has promptly distributed medicine to various hospitals and clinics
for their treatment," he added.
--
